Storyline:

The Enterprise searches the reportedly primitive and warlike planet Ekos for the
missing Federation cultural observer Professor John Gill. When Kirk and Spock
beam down, they find the Ekosians have turned into a Nazi society, with Gill as
their Fuhrer, and are at war with the peaceful people of neighboring planet Zeon.
They steal uniforms to enter the headquarters; but when Spock is forced to remove
his helmet, his ears betray them and they are led straight to the torture chamber.
After a flogging as Zeon spies, they manage to escape with a Zeon prisoner, who
takes them to the Zeon resistance. The resistance tests them, and plots with an
Ekosian defector just to reach Gill, posing as a Nazi propaganda film crew. Once
they enter inside, they discover things are not quite as they appear.
